** Below are the commands you need to run in a terminal to download and start suricata on the splunking server. you will need internet connectivity to the blade. run the below as root**
**download suricata rpm to opt**

yum install epel-release yum-plugin-copr
yum copr enable @oisf/suricata-6.0
./configure | grep yum
*yum install whatever the grep command returns*
pip3 install pyyaml
./configure
make install-full
*edit the suricata.yaml file to have the interfaces you want to collect on. search for memcap until you get to stream section, replace value with 256mb*
/usr/bin/suricta -c /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml -i em2
